title: U.S. wind power generation 2000 to 2018
yAxis: Net generation in billion kilowatt hours
summary: This is a line chart with an x axis representing Year and a y axis representing Net generation in billion kilowatt hours, containing a total of 19 data points.
In general Net generation in billion kilowatt hours has rose over the Year.

Net generation in billion kilowatt hours is roughly increasing from 2000 to 2002, roughly constant from 2002 to 2003, rapidly increasing from 2003 to 2012, and lastly roughly constant from 2012 to 2018.
Maximum Net generation in billion kilowatt hours, about 274.95 was reported at Year 2018
Minimum Net generation in billion kilowatt hours about 5.59 was reached at Year 2000
